entries.femaleVariant: Um... Johnny? Pretty sure they turned your great spot into a slurp shop.
Mindless fuckin' consumerism wins the day again.
Lookin' for some Samurai tapes.
Know anything about bootlegs from the Rainbow Cadenza days? Like, say, dunno... Samurai stuff?
entries.maleVariant: Know anything about any bootlegs from the Rainbow Cadenza days? Like, say, I dunno... Samurai stuff?

entries.femaleVariant: Samurai, Samurai... Oh, that ugly red face on black? Yeah, even I know that one.
Old guy comes by here sometimes, wearing their shirt. Spends the whole time yakking with his psychofan friends.
Wouldn't happen to know where I could find 'im?
Huh... This is why you don't bring back fallen warriors.
Sooner or later, they're gonna see everything they fought for's turned to shit.
What happened to Rainbow Cadenza?
Hey. "Rainbow Cadenza" mean anything to you?
entries.maleVariant: Uh, hey. Um, "Rainbow Cadenza" mean anything to you?

entries.femaleVariant: Oh no, another one. Aren't you too young for this?
Too what now?
Every day, some sad grandpa in his old leather comes in here, asks where is his old rainbow club.
And I am like a broken record, tell all of them the corp bought them out twenty years ago. Ehh... I should put up a sign.
entries.maleVariant: And I am like a broken record, tell all of them the corp bought 'em out twenty years ago. Ehh... I should put up a sign.

entries.femaleVariant: You can find him living back in the twenty-twenties, heh. But besides that, he's out there, at the market.
Preem. Thanks.
Point for the other team, huh?
What's he sell?
Does his shoppin' there?
What's he sellin'?
Meanin' he does his shopping there?
He sells ancient, dusty tapes of ancient, dusty indie bands. No one's heard of a single one of them.
Ganic strawberries 'n' cream. What do you think?
I mean you can do yours at his spot. Assuming you'd even want to.
